modules.description: This module manipulates and generates OCaml expressions for conditional logging, primarily used during PPX extension expansion. It provides functions to construct and inline logging expressions that respect typechecking, including null operations and dynamic log calls. Concrete use cases include embedding debug prints that are type-safe and optionally disabled at compile time.

This module controls logging behavior through a mutable `enabled` flag and provides an `extractor` function that processes AST patterns to generate logging expressions. It works with OCaml's abstract syntax tree (AST) structures, particularly payloads and expressions, to enable conditional logging during compilation. Concrete use cases include injecting debug logging into generated code based on the `enabled` flag and transforming AST nodes to include log statements.

This module provides type-safe conditional logging within OCaml code, primarily during PPX expansion. It manipulates OCaml AST structures to embed compile-time controlled logging expressions directly into generated code. Concrete use cases include injecting debug statements that can be selectively disabled at compile time without runtime overhead.
